column44: STRATIGRAPHIC RELATIONS: From the Kaili Fm, which overlies the Tsinghsutung Fm (Duyunian), and is overlain by the Jialao Fm (Taijiangian). column27: SPECIFIC LOCATION: Songtao County, Guizhou Province, South China. Section located on the eastern limb of the dissected Songtao Anticline.
column44: Lower Cambrian successions are well exposed and consist of the (uppermost) Proterozoic Liuchapo and the basal Cambrian Qingshudong formations. The Jiumenchong Formation conformably overlies the Liuchapo Formation, which consists of black silicolites (cherts) and phosphatic siliceous shales. The Jiumenchong Formation is subdivided into two members. The lower member consists of black shale yielding bivalved arthropods (Sunella) and tubular fossils (Sphenothallus) 15 m above the base of the formation. The upper member consists of dark gray argillaceous limestone with trilobites, including Hupeidiscus sp., Sinodiscus changyangensis, and Metaredlichia sp.

column44: Cambrian Stage 3
column45: Hongjingshao Formation is marked by the first appearance of thick-bedded coarse sandstones (Fig. 1c). At the Xiazhuang section, only the lower part of the Hongjingshao Formation, ~50 m-thick sandstone and siltstone intercalated by a few layers of yellowish mudstone, is exposed. The soft-bodied fossils are uncovered from these intercalated mudstone layers.

column45: Here the Ediacaran??Cambrian contact is developed as a disconformity surface in the upper part of the Dengying Formation (Xie, 1988); the Ediacaran blocky dolostones are overlain by 8.4 m of thick intercalated dark grey bioclastic limestones and silty dolostones of the lower Cambrian Xihaoping Member (Fig. 1C). The Xihaoping Member is overlain at another disconformity, by 116 m rocks of the Shuijingtuo Formation, which is subdivided into two informal units. The lower unit, 31 m thick, is composed of dark, thin, silty limestones, while the upper unit is composed of 85 m of siltstones interbedded with thin limestone layers.
